        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Assistance Program for the Cultivation of Lotus Fruit (Dragon Fruit)&amp;quot; introduced by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Department, Gujarat, aims to promote horticultural farming by supporting farmers with financial aid for the initial infrastructure and planting costs involved in dragon fruit cultivation.\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n- **General category:** 50% assistance or up to ₹3,00,000/- per hectare (whichever is less).- **SC/ST** **category:**  75% assistance or up to ₹4,50,000/- per hectare (whichever is less).\n> **First Year Assistance:**\n\n\n- **Cement pole/pipe:** 1111 units at ₹300 each = ₹3,33,300/-- **Planting material:** 4444 units at ₹35 each = ₹1,55,540/-- **Total:** ₹4,88,840/-- **Actual Assistance Provided:** 50% or up to ₹2,44,420/-, whichever is less.\n> **Second Year Assistance:**\n\n\n- **Head ring or Trellising &amp; wire (approx. 400 kg)**: ₹1,11,160/-- **Actual Assistance Provided:** 50% or up to ₹55,580/-, whichever is less.\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme provides financial assistance to farmers to support the cultivation of dragon fruit (lotus fruit), with higher benefits for SC/ST and priority for small-scale and women farmers.",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
